      "detector": "review",
      "file": ".",
      "tier": 3,
      "confidence": "high",
      "summary": "Region and retrieve APIs have overlapping names but materially different side effects, weakening API discoverability.",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "api_surface_coherence",
        "related_files": [
          "goseg/startram/startram.go",
          "README.md"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "FetchRegions() is read-only, SyncRegions() mutates package-global Regions, and GetRegions() is a compatibility alias for FetchRegions() despite getter naming usually implying cached read.",
          "Retrieve() is read-only, while SyncRetrieve() mutates config.StartramConfig, may mutate persisted config via UpdateConf, and emits EventBus events.",
          "README does not document backend naming/side-effect conventions, so callers have to inspect implementation to know mutation behavior."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Refactor to explicit verb contracts (`Load*` for pure fetch, `Refresh*` for state mutation) and document side effects in exported API docs and README backend section; deprecate ambiguous aliases like GetRegions().",
        "reasoning": ""
      },
