      "id": "review::.::holistic::cross_module_architecture::startram_god_module_boundary_collapse::ffb5fa26",
      "detector": "review",
      "file": ".",
      "tier": 3,
      "confidence": "high",
      "summary": "The `startram` package is a hub module spanning unrelated layers, collapsing boundaries between transport, persistence, system, and domain workflows.",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "cross_module_architecture",
        "related_files": [
          "goseg/startram/startram.go",
          "goseg/config/version.go"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "`startram.go` combines remote API orchestration (`http.Get/Post`), config mutation (`config.UpdateConf`, `config.Conf`), event broadcasting (`EventBus <- ...`), Docker shell execution (`exec.Command`), backup extraction (`tar`, `zstd`), and crypto (`aes/gcm`).",
          "The pattern mirrors config-side shared-state orchestration (`version.go` manages remote fetch + persistence + process-level readiness flags), indicating architectural responsibilities are centralized in package hubs instead of separated services."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Split `startram` into boundary-focused components: API client, registration service, backup service, and event adapter. Introduce dependency-injected interfaces so side effects (config writes, event publish, shell/system calls) are delegated to adapters rather than embedded in domain flow.",
        "reasoning": ""
      },
