    "review::.::holistic::abstraction_fitness::duplicated_wireguard_recovery_orchestration::390620b5": {
      "id": "review::.::holistic::abstraction_fitness::duplicated_wireguard_recovery_orchestration::390620b5",
      "detector": "review",
      "file": ".",
      "tier": 3,
      "confidence": "high",
      "summary": "Wireguard restart/recovery flow is copy-pasted across handlers and routines instead of abstracted once.",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "abstraction_fitness",
        "related_files": [
          "goseg/handler/startram.go",
          "goseg/routines/docker.go"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "`handleStartramRestart` in `goseg/handler/startram.go` builds `wgShips`, restarts wireguard, stops ships (`click.BarExit`/`WaitForShipExit`), deletes ship+minio containers, then calls `docker.LoadUrbits`, `docker.LoadMC`, and `docker.LoadMinIOs`.",
          "`Check502Loop` in `goseg/routines/docker.go` repeats the same orchestration sequence when a second 502 strike occurs.",
          "Both implementations encode the same policy but diverge in error aggregation/reporting style, increasing drift risk when restart behavior changes."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Extract a single orchestrator (for example `docker.RecoverWireguardFleet(ctx, opts)`) that owns ship discovery, stop/delete/recreate sequencing, and error policy. Call it from both `handleStartramRestart` and `Check502Loop` with scenario-specific options.",
        "reasoning": ""
      },
      "status": "auto_resolved",
      "note": "Disappeared from scan \u2014 likely fixed",
      "first_seen": "2026-03-01T13:23:44+00:00",
