    "review::.::holistic::abstraction_fitness::shipcreator_pass_through_interface::58f5127c": {
      "id": "review::.::holistic::abstraction_fitness::shipcreator_pass_through_interface::58f5127c",
      "detector": "review",
      "file": ".",
      "tier": 3,
      "confidence": "medium",
      "summary": "Shipcreator\u2019s config interface is a mostly pass-through wrapper with one concrete implementation.",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "abstraction_fitness",
        "related_files": [
          "goseg/shipcreator/shipcreator.go",
          "goseg/config/config.go"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "`ConfigService` in `goseg/shipcreator/shipcreator.go` is implemented only by `configService`, whose methods directly forward to `config` package functions (`Conf`, `UrbitConf`, `UrbitConfAll`, `UpdateUrbitConfig`, `UpdateConfTyped`).",
          "This interface adds call indirection but little policy/translation logic; the abstraction boundary does not represent a distinct domain model.",
          "A package-global `defaultService` further hides construction and keeps static coupling to global config behavior."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Either remove the pass-through interface and call `config` directly, or strengthen the abstraction by introducing a true repository/service contract with focused methods that encode ship-creation invariants (ports, persistence, pier list mutation) instead of forwarding raw config operations.",
        "reasoning": ""
      },
      "status": "auto_resolved",
      "note": "not reported in latest holistic re-import",
