          "goseg/routines/docker.go",
          "goseg/routines/version.go"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "In `wireguard.go`, many functions are duplicated (`LoadWireguard/loadWireguard`, `wgContainerConf/wgContainerConfWithRuntime`, `buildWgConf/buildWgConfWithRuntime`, `WriteWgConf/writeWgConfWithRuntime`, file-copy helpers).",
          "Same pattern appears in `netdata.go`, `minio.go`, `routines/docker.go`, and `routines/version.go`, creating two call paths per behavior.",
          "Runtime structs include function fields that point to local wrappers (`writeWgConf: writeWgConfWithRuntime`, `writeNDConf: writeNDConfWithRuntime`), increasing conceptual load and making ownership of side effects harder to track."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Consolidate behind one explicit runtime boundary per subsystem: keep internal runtime-injected methods for tests, but expose one production entrypoint per operation and collapse duplicate wrapper layers. Consider constructor-injected service structs over free-function pairs.",
