      "file": ".",
      "tier": 3,
      "confidence": "high",
      "summary": "WiFi subsystem combines unrelated concerns in one module with broad mutable global state.",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "design_coherence",
        "related_files": [
          "goseg/system/wifi.go",
          "goseg/handler/handler.go",
          "goseg/accesspoint/accesspoint_test.go"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "`wifi.go` owns websocket client map and message loop (`CaptiveAPI`), captive portal lifecycle, AP mode toggling, command execution (`nmcli`, `systemctl`, `ip`, `reboot`), and periodic discovery loops in one file.",
          "Global mutable package state (`clients`, `WifiInfo`, `Device`, `ConfChannel`, `c2cEnabled`) is updated by long-running loops and request handlers, increasing hidden coupling and lifecycle complexity.",
          "`handler.C2CHandler` delegates directly into this mixed module, so UI-triggered connect flow is tightly bound to OS/network orchestration details."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Separate WiFi concerns into focused components: command runner/device discovery, AP/captive control, and websocket transport adapter; expose a small service interface for C2C actions and state updates.",
        "reasoning": ""
