      "tier": 3,
      "confidence": "high",
      "summary": "Several mutating workflows swallow operation failures and still return success, leaving partial state changes unreported.",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "error_consistency",
        "related_files": [
          "goseg/handler/urbit_operations.go",
          "goseg/handler/newship.go",
          "goseg/routines/backup.go"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "`urbit_operations.go` logs service/config/broadcast update failures during delete/export/rebuild flows and still returns `nil` in success path (lines 578-597, 619-622, 720-727).",
          "`newship.go` logs failures while removing config/volume and does not propagate cleanup failures (lines 264-274); `os.RemoveAll` is called without checking error (line 279).",
          "`backup.go` logs failed remote uploads and continues loop without surfacing scheduler failure (lines 81-84)."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Define a shared policy for mutating operations: classify errors as recoverable vs terminal, accumulate recoverable failures, and return a non-nil error (or explicit partial-failure result) whenever required side effects fail.",
