        ],
        "evidence": [
          "Each module defines large runtime structs of function fields (`wireguardRuntime`, `netdataRuntime`, `minioRuntime`, `urbitRuntime`, `versionRuntime`, `dockerRoutineRuntime`) plus `new*Runtime()` constructors with repeated wiring of globals.",
          "Many exported functions are thin wrappers (`LoadWireguard`, `WriteWgConf`, `LoadNetdata`, `WriteNDConf`, `LoadMinIOs`, `LoadUrbits`, `CheckVersionLoop`, `DockerSubscriptionHandler`) that only call `*WithRuntime(new*Runtime())`."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Extract a shared seam strategy: keep seam injection only at subsystem entrypoints, and collapse repetitive `newRuntime + withRuntime` scaffolding into reusable factories or a smaller number of explicit interfaces per subsystem.",
