          "goseg/handler/urbit_operations.go",
          "goseg/routines/docker.go",
          "goseg/broadcast/broadcast.go"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "`config.Conf()` returns full global config and is consumed directly in unrelated concerns (auth session state, orchestration, docker health loops), e.g., `auth.Initialize`, `ValidateAndAuthorizeRequestToken`, `routines.check502Loop`.",
          "Modules mix narrow snapshot helpers (`StartramSettingsSnapshot`, `ConnectivitySettingsSnapshot`) with direct global config and per-ship calls (`config.UrbitConf`, `config.UpdateConfTyped`), indicating no stable boundary.",
          "`broadcast.assembleUrbitView` and handler flows repeatedly pull config values from multiple global getters instead of receiving domain-scoped settings objects."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Define small read/write ports per domain (auth settings, startram settings, ship runtime settings) and migrate modules from `Conf()`/global bag access to those ports; reserve `Conf()` for internal config package use.",
