    "review::.::holistic::high_level_elegance::wifi_adapter_mixes_transport_and_system_orchestration::88a5660e": {
      "id": "review::.::holistic::high_level_elegance::wifi_adapter_mixes_transport_and_system_orchestration::88a5660e",
      "detector": "review",
      "file": ".",
      "tier": 3,
      "confidence": "high",
      "summary": "The Wi\u2011Fi transport adapter owns unrelated layers (websocket transport, command semantics, and process restart policy), blurring subsystem ownership boundaries.",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "high_level_elegance",
        "related_files": [
          "goseg/system/wifi_transport_adapter.go",
          "goseg/uploadsvc/service.go"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "captiveTransportAdapter manages websocket upgrader/client registry/read loop and also performs command interpretation in `processMessage`.",
          "`processMessage` triggers infrastructure side effects via `connectToWiFi` and `restartGroundSeg`, while `restartGroundSegService` shells out to `systemctl restart groundseg`.",
          "In contrast, uploadsvc/service.go separates command dispatch behind `Executor` and `Service`, highlighting that system package bypasses a comparable application-service seam."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Extract a captive portal application service that receives typed commands and owns Wi\u2011Fi/restart orchestration, while keeping `captiveTransportAdapter` limited to transport concerns (decode/encode, connection lifecycle). Route `processMessage` through that service instead of performing side effects directly.",
        "reasoning": ""
      },
      "status": "open",
      "note": null,
      "first_seen": "2026-03-01T15:37:31+00:00",
      "last_seen": "2026-03-01T15:37:31+00:00",
      "resolved_at": null,
      "reopen_count": 0,
      "lang": "go",
      "suppressed": false,
      "suppressed_at": null,
      "suppression_pattern": null
    },
    "review::.::holistic::high_level_elegance::action_contracts_have_split_and_inconsistent_ownership::eb173154": {
      "id": "review::.::holistic::high_level_elegance::action_contracts_have_split_and_inconsistent_ownership::eb173154",
      "detector": "review",
      "file": ".",
      "tier": 3,
      "confidence": "medium",
      "summary": "Action contract definition is inconsistent and partially duplicated, reducing predictability of top-level behavior ownership.",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "high_level_elegance",
        "related_files": [
          "goseg/system/wifi_transport_adapter.go",
          "goseg/uploadsvc/service.go",
          "goseg/uploadsvc/adapters/upload_payload_test.go"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "wifi transport uses raw string matching (`payload.Payload.Action != \"connect\"`) with no typed contract.",
          "uploadsvc defines typed actions (`ActionOpenEndpoint`, `ActionReset`) plus `UnsupportedActionError`, but also keeps a separate global `supportedActions` slice and dispatch map in `Executor`.",
          "adapter test asserts mapping by converting action constants to/from strings, showing cross-layer dependence on literal protocol values instead of a single canonical action contract owner."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Standardize action handling on a single contract pattern: define typed action enums plus parse/validate helpers at boundary adapters, and make one source of truth for supported actions (derive from dispatch or registration API, not parallel lists).",
        "reasoning": ""
      },
      "status": "open",
      "note": null,
      "first_seen": "2026-03-01T15:37:31+00:00",
      "last_seen": "2026-03-01T15:37:31+00:00",
      "resolved_at": null,
      "reopen_count": 0,
      "lang": "go",
      "suppressed": false,
      "suppressed_at": null,
      "suppression_pattern": null
    },
    "review::.::holistic::abstraction_fitness::global-singleton-function-bag-seams::109b7dae": {
      "id": "review::.::holistic::abstraction_fitness::global-singleton-function-bag-seams::109b7dae",
      "detector": "review",
      "file": ".",
      "tier": 3,
      "confidence": "high",
      "summary": "Global singleton state plus wide function-bag runtimes creates high indirection without clear domain boundaries.",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "abstraction_fitness",
        "related_files": [
          "goseg/config/config.go",
          "goseg/docker/runtime_seams.go",
          "goseg/routines/runtime_seams.go",
          "goseg/main.go"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "`config` exposes mutable globals and does heavy init-time setup in `init()`; many packages read/write through this shared state.",
          "`dockerRuntime` and `routineRuntime` each carry dozens of function fields and mostly re-export package calls, indicating indirection wrappers instead of cohesive service contracts.",
          "Entry points wire subsystems through globals rather than explicit lifecycle-scoped dependencies."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Introduce cohesive service interfaces (e.g., ConfigStore, ContainerRuntime, TransitionPublisher) with constructor injection; reduce runtime structs to capability-focused dependencies and phase out direct use of mutable config globals.",
        "reasoning": ""
      },
      "status": "open",
      "note": null,
      "first_seen": "2026-03-01T15:37:31+00:00",
      "last_seen": "2026-03-01T15:37:31+00:00",
      "resolved_at": null,
      "reopen_count": 0,
      "lang": "go",
      "suppressed": false,
      "suppressed_at": null,
      "suppression_pattern": null
    },
    "review::.::holistic::abstraction_fitness::test-seams-rely-on-global-mutation::8f85d4c3": {
      "id": "review::.::holistic::abstraction_fitness::test-seams-rely-on-global-mutation::8f85d4c3",
      "detector": "review",
      "file": ".",
      "tier": 3,
      "confidence": "high",
      "summary": "Tests depend on mutating package globals, showing production seams are not explicit or isolated.",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "abstraction_fitness",
        "related_files": [
          "goseg/docker/wireguard_test.go",
          "goseg/routines/version_test.go",
          "goseg/rectify/rectify_test.go",
          "goseg/config/config.go"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "`TestWriteWgConfCreateAndUpdate` mutates `config.DockerDir` globally.",
          "Version tests mutate global `config.Architecture`.",
          "Rectify tests replace global channel `leak.LeakChan` to keep handlers unblocked."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Move mutable process config and channels behind injectable test fixtures/interfaces so tests can provide local instances without cross-test global rewiring.",
        "reasoning": ""
      },
      "status": "open",
      "note": null,
      "first_seen": "2026-03-01T15:37:31+00:00",
